explores the renewed relevance of oligarchy to contemporary global politics. By drawing out lessons from classic texts, contributors illustrate how the character of oligarchical regimes informs contemporary political life. Topics include the relationship between the American government and corporations, the tension between republican and oligarchical regimes, and the potential conflicts that have opened up between economic management and political life. On Oligarchy deftly illuminates the significance of this regime in the context of pressing global economic and political issues.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aBagby, Laurie M. Johnson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBradshaw, Leah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Craig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKellow, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoivukoski, Toivo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoivukoski, Toivu, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNeill, Jeremy S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewell, Waller R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSikkenga, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSimpson, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkultety, Steven C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTabachnick, David Edward, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeixeira, Herminio Meireles, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/97814426